{"title_page": "Sakawa", "text_new": "{{about|a Ghanaian phenomenon|the town in Japan|Sakawa, K\u014dchi}}\n\n'''Sakawa''' is a Ghanaian term for illegal practices which combine modern Internet-based fraud with African traditionalist rituals.The term or word Sakawa is an Hausa word which means ''putting inside''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-africa-32583161|title=Inside the world of Ghana's internet fraudsters|last=Darko|first=Sammy|date=10 May 2015|website=bbc.co.uk|publisher=BBC|accessdate=4 March 2017|via=www.bbc.co.uk}}</ref> <ref>{{Cite news|last=Darko|first=Sammy|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-africa-32583161|title=Inside the world of Ghana's internet fraudsters|date=2015-05-10|work=BBC News|access-date=2020-04-02|language=en-GB}}</ref>The rituals, which are mostly in the form of sacrifices, are intended to spiritually manipulate victims so that the scammer's fraud is successful.  The term Sakawa referred to specific online scams but has since broadened to include all types of [[419 scams|online frauds]] and scams mainly targeting foreigners. The scammers flaunt stylish clothes, luxury cars, and enormous wealth, in order to promote this act. In impoverished areas, it can be seen as a way of survival for some.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=o26Eks801oc |title=Internet Scamming in Ghana |publisher=YouTube |date= |accessdate=2013-12-05}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Abubakar |first=Zulaihatu |url=http://www.modernghana.com/news/419261/1/sakawa-guy-confesses.html |title=Sakawa Guy Confesses |publisher=Modern Ghana |date=2012-09-22 |accessdate=2013-12-05}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ghanaweb.com/GhanaHomePage/NewsArchive/artikel.php?ID=260823 |title=Six teenagers engage in mysterious Sakawa deal &#124; General News 2012-12-30 |publisher=GhanaWeb |date=2012-12-30 |accessdate=2013-12-05}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Akwetey-Okunor |first=Isaac |url=http://thechronicle.com.gh/sakawa-coffin-exhibited-in-public/ |title=Sakawa coffin exhibited in public &#124; Ghanaian Chronicle |publisher=The Ghanaian Chronicle |date=2012-06-22 |accessdate=2013-12-05}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://graphic.com.gh/archive/features/the-sakawa-menace-any-solutions.html |title=The sakawa menace ...Any solutions &#124; features |publisher=Daily Graphic |last=Dzandu |first=Sammy |date=2013-06-03 |accessdate=2013-12-05}}</ref>\n\nScammers involved in this practice call themselves Sakawa boys.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Darko |first1=Sammy |title=Inside the world of Ghana's internet fraudsters |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-africa-32583161 |website=BBC |accessdate=19 March 2020}}</ref> A culture has developed around Sakawa which has influenced music and clothing brands. Movies depicting the lifestyle have become popular, a movement lead by Ghanaian filmaker [[Socrate Safo]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Thomas |first1=Morton |title=The Sakawa Boys: Inside the Bizarre Criminal World of Ghana\u2019s Cyber-Juju Email Scam Gangs |url=https://www.vice.com/en_us/article/4xx393/the-sakawa-boys-inside-the-bizarre-criminal-world-of-ghanas-cyber-juju-email-scam-gangs |website=Vice |language=en |date=5 April 2011}}</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n*[[Crime in Ghana]]\n*[[Nigerian scam]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [https://motherboard.vice.com/en_us/article/4xx393/the-sakawa-boys-inside-the-bizarre-criminal-world-of-ghanas-cyber-juju-email-scam-gangs The Sakawa Boys], a documentary about the phenomenon.\n*[http://www.tripwire.com/state-of-security/off-topic/a-look-at-the-real-social-engineers/ A Look at the Real African Social Engineers], an article on Sakawa culture.\n*[http://www.tripwire.com/state-of-security/security-awareness/the-anatomy-of-a-scam/ The Anatomy Of a Sakawa Scam], an article detailing sakawa type frauds.\n\n[[Category:Crime in Ghana]]\n[[Category:Internet fraud]]\n[[Category:African witchcraft]]\n[[Category:Telecommunications in Ghana]]\n[[Category:Crimes involving Satanism or the occult]]\n\n{{ghana-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{about|a Ghanaian phenomenon|the town in Japan|Sakawa, K\u014dchi}}\n\n'''Sakawa''' is a Ghanaian term for illegal practices which combine modern Internet-based fraud with African traditionalist rituals.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-africa-32583161|title=Inside the world of Ghana's internet fraudsters|last=Darko|first=Sammy|date=10 May 2015|website=bbc.co.uk|publisher=BBC|accessdate=4 March 2017|via=www.bbc.co.uk}}</ref> The rituals, which are mostly in the form of sacrifices, are intended to spiritually manipulate victims so that the scammer's fraud is successful.  The term Sakawa referred to specific online scams but has since broadened to include all types of [[419 scams|online frauds]] and scams mainly targeting foreigners. The scammers flaunt stylish clothes, luxury cars, and enormous wealth, in order to promote this act. In impoverished areas, it can be seen as a way of survival for some.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=o26Eks801oc |title=Internet Scamming in Ghana |publisher=YouTube |date= |accessdate=2013-12-05}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Abubakar |first=Zulaihatu |url=http://www.modernghana.com/news/419261/1/sakawa-guy-confesses.html |title=Sakawa Guy Confesses |publisher=Modern Ghana |date=2012-09-22 |accessdate=2013-12-05}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ghanaweb.com/GhanaHomePage/NewsArchive/artikel.php?ID=260823 |title=Six teenagers engage in mysterious Sakawa deal &#124; General News 2012-12-30 |publisher=GhanaWeb |date=2012-12-30 |accessdate=2013-12-05}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Akwetey-Okunor |first=Isaac |url=http://thechronicle.com.gh/sakawa-coffin-exhibited-in-public/ |title=Sakawa coffin exhibited in public &#124; Ghanaian Chronicle |publisher=The Ghanaian Chronicle |date=2012-06-22 |accessdate=2013-12-05}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://graphic.com.gh/archive/features/the-sakawa-menace-any-solutions.html |title=The sakawa menace ...Any solutions &#1